LEADER CARD WORKS v. OTTEN BROTHERS COMPANY et al. No. 7604. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Jan. 6, 1937. Warren G. Wheeler, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellant. Harness, Dickey, Pierce & Hann, of Detroit, Mich., for appellees.

Before MOORMAN, HICKS, and SIMONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It appearing to the court that a motion and stipulation to docket and dismiss appeal has been filed; accompanied by certificate of the clerk as provided by rule 18,

■ On consideration whereof it is ordered that the appeal be, and- the same is hereby, docketed and dismissed.
